abstract: The reports come as Qantas Airways said that one of its Boeing 747s had to return to Australia on Monday after experiencing electrical problems.
snippet: The reports come as Qantas Airways said that one of its Boeing 747s had to return to Australia on Monday after experiencing electrical problems.
lead_paragraph: PARIS  Airline industry executives said Monday that an extensive inspection and replacement program of Rolls-Royce engines on their Airbus A380 fleets could potentially lead to a shortage of available spares.

headline.main: Airlines Worry Over Possible Shortage of A380 Engine Spares
headline.print_headline: Airlines Worry Over Possible Shortage of A380 Engine Spares
